.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-RENDER" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.1.16" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-render \- Render the generated sbatch script
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose render [OPTIONS]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Render the sbatch script produced from the normalized plan. Use this to inspect generated SBATCH directives, srun invocations, mounts, and environment forwarding without submitting the job.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB-f\fR, \fB--file\fR \fIFILE\fR
Compose specification file to read. Default: compose.yaml.
.TP
\fB-o\fR, \fB--output\fR \fIOUTPUT\fR
Write the rendered batch script to this path instead of stdout.
.TP
\fB--format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format. Possible values: text, json.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
hpc\-compose render \-f compose.yaml
hpc\-compose render \-f compose.yaml \-\-output job.sbatch
hpc\-compose render \-f compose.yaml \-\-format json
.fi
